"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/452074","Home Office","false","2016-02-22","<p>An answer is still being prepared. We are currently extracting the data and need to ensure it is correctly quality checked to give the Hon. Member an accurate response and I will write to the honourable Member when it is finished.</p>","Staffordshire Moorlands","Karen Bradley",,"2016-02-22T16:38:19.83Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/452074/answer","Biography information for Karen Bradley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/452074/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/452074/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-02-10","Asylum: EU Law","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many people have been transferred from the UK to (a) Italy, (b) Hungary, (c) Croatia, (d) France, (e) Belgium, (f) Austria and (g) Germany under the Dublin III Regulation in the last 12 months.","false","Biography information for Thangam Debbonaire","Bristol West","Thangam Debbonaire","26925"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/452075","Department for International Development","false","2016-02-22","<p>The UK’s International Climate Fund is jointly managed by DFID, DECC and Defra and has already directly supported 15 million people to cope with effects of climate change and given 2.6 million people improved access to clean energy.</p><p>The new UK Aid Strategy brings together the Government’s poverty reduction objectives with a commitment to tackle some of today’s biggest global challenges, including climate change. Tackling climate change and promoting sustainable development are two sides of the same coin – we cannot achieve one without the other.</p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd",,"2016-02-22T13:27:13.967Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/452075/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/452075/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/452075/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2016-02-10","Developing Countries: Climate Change","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, how her Department is working with the Department for Energy and Climate Change to ensure that official development assistance funding provided for international climate projects is prioritised in policies aimed at reducing poverty.","false","Biography information for Rushanara Ali","Bethnal Green and Bow","Rushanara Ali","26724"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/452076","Department for International Development","false","2016-02-22","<p>DFID, and related non-departmental public bodies, do not offer home to work travel allowance, car allowance or subsidised health insurance to staff</p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd",,"2016-02-22T14:59:01.823Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/452076/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/452076/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/452076/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2016-02-10","Department for International Development: Fringe Benefits","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, how many staff in her Department and its non-departmental public bodies receive (a) home to work travel allowance, (b) a car allowance and (c) subsidised health insurance.","false","Biography information for Philip Davies","Shipley","Philip Davies","26821"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/452077","Department for International Development","false","2016-02-22","<p>To date, the UK has committed £79.5 million to the humanitarian crisis in Iraq. UK aid is reaching hundreds of thousands of people across Iraq, including the most vulnerable groups, such as Yezidis. All UK-funded aid is distributed on the basis of needs and in line with humanitarian principles which ensure that no-one is discriminated against on the grounds of race, religion or ethnicity . According to the International Organisation for Migration, the vast majority of Internally Displaced Persons (IDPs) in Iraq live in host communities, with around 10% of all Iraqi IDPs living in camps.</p><p> </p><p>On a field visit to Dohuk in January 2016, DFID officials met with a number of displaced Iraqis, including Yezidis, and discussed their shelter needs and living conditions. This included members of the Yezidi community who were living in poor conditions in informal settlements. The DFID team were told that the UN High Commission for Refugees (UNHCR) had undertaken to relocate these individuals to a camp with appropriate services and conditions. However, this offer had been declined by Yezidi heads of households because of a perception that the camps were too far from employment opportunities although it appeared that other members of the community held differing views about the suitability of the camps.</p><p> </p>","New Forest West","Mr Desmond Swayne",,"2016-02-22T15:03:36.09Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/452077/answer","Biography information for Sir Desmond Swayne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/452077/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/452077/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2016-02-10","Iraq: Yazidis","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what recent assessment she has made of the living conditions of the Yazidi community in refugee camps in Iraq.","false","Biography information for Hilary Benn","Leeds Central","Hilary Benn","26921"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/452078","Department for International Development","false","2016-02-22","<p>Through the cross-Departmental Conflict Stability and Security Fund (CSSF), the UK has allocated £10 million in Iraq for 2015/16 to fund security and stabilisation work.</p><p>£2.5 million of this support has been pledged to the UN Development Programme’s (UNDP) Funding Facility for Immediate Stabilisation (FFIS). The FFIS is the principle mechanism for international support to stabilisation in Iraq and works to priorities set by the Iraqi authorities.</p><p>Assessments in Sinjar by the UNDP and other partners are proceeding. It is expected that FFIS-supported stabilisation activities will start in the near future.</p>","New Forest West","Mr Desmond Swayne",,"2016-02-22T13:31:27.863Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/452078/answer","Biography information for Sir Desmond Swayne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/452078/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/452078/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2016-02-10","Iraq: Reconstruction","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what assistance the UK is providing for reconstruction of Sinjar in Iraq.","false","Biography information for Hilary Benn","Leeds Central","Hilary Benn","26919"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/452079","Ministry of Justice","false","2016-02-26","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the reply given to my hon. Friend the hon. Member for Gower on 28<sup>th</sup> September 2015, which can be found at: <a href="http://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-question/Commons/2015-09-09/9735/" target="_blank">http://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-question/Commons/2015-09-09/9735/</a></p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"2016-02-26T12:38:34.637Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/452079/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/452079/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/452079/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2016-02-10","Corruption","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what progress his Department has made on Action 36 of the UK Anti-Corruption plan, published in December 2014, relating to corporate criminal liability.","false","Biography information for Mr Jonathan Djanogly","Huntingdon","Mr Jonathan Djanogly","26916"
