s of the public during each Astral exercise between February 2011 and November 2012.","false","Biography information for Brendan O'Hara","Argyll and Bute","Brendan O'Hara","26647"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451614","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-02-16","<p>I am withholding the requested information as its disclosure would or would be likely to prejudice national security and international relations.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"2016-02-16T16:01:50.597Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451614/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451614/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451614/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-02-09","Military Exercises: Nuclear Weapons","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what (a) atmospheric stability class was assumed for the downwind dispersion and deposition of the release fall-out; and what the assumed distribution and gross area of ground and surface contamination was in terms of contours versed in Becqueral per square metre in each Astral exercise between February 2011 and November 2012.","false","Biography information for Brendan O'Hara","Argyll and Bute","Brendan O'Hara","26648"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451615","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-02-16","<p>The Ministry of Defence maintains a Defence Nuclear Emergency Organisation (NEO) to respond in the unlikely event of an emergency involving the transport of defence nuclear materials. The NEO organises regular exercises to test the effectiveness of its emergency response planning and arrangements. These include the Astral series of exercises, which are designed to be challenging, and thus simulate the extremely unlikely event of a release of radioactive material from the transport containers. No radioactive materials are used or released to the environment during the exercises. The specific exercise objectives do not require assessments or estimates of decontamination, environmental or other post-incident decontamination costs or of radiological dose uptakes. The Atomic Weapons Establishment (AWE) undertook the modelling for each Astral exercise between February 2011 and November 2012.</p><p>I am withholding information about the physical state, mass quantity, release fraction and total released radioactivity assumed for these exercises as disclosure would or would be likely to prejudice national security.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt","26645 ; 26646 ; 26647 ; 26649","2016-02-16T16:05:33.87Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451615/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451615/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451615/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-02-09","Military Exercises: Nuclear Weapons","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, whether each Astral exercise between February 2011 and November 2012 assumed a post-incident release of nuclear materials from the transportation packages.","false","Biography information for Brendan O'Hara","Argyll and Bute","Brendan O'Hara","26650"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451616","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-02-15","<p>The number and average wage of civilians employed by the Ministry of Defence (MOD) at the listed sites is not held centrally and could be provided only at disproportionate cost.</p><p>MOD does not hold figures relating to the employees of contractors by site. The number of civilians employed by the consortium AWE Management Ltd is 155.</p>","Sevenoaks","Michael Fallon","26656","2016-02-15T15:51:00.887Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451616/answer","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451616/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451616/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-02-09","Defence: Civilians","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many civilians are employed by the (a) Ministry of Defence and its trading bodies and (b) contractors at (i) AWE Aldemaston; (ii) AWE Burghfield; (iii) BAE Systems Maritime-Submarines at Barrow-in-Furness; (iv) Babcock at Devonport and (v) Rolls-Royce at Raynewsay, Derby; and how many such employees are employed by AWE Management Limited.","false","Biography information for Neil Gray","Airdrie and Shotts","Neil Gray","26655"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451617","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-02-15","<p>The number and average wage of civilians employed by the Ministry of Defence (MOD) at the listed sites is not held centrally and could be provided only at disproportionate cost.</p><p>MOD does not hold figures relating to the employees of contractors by site. The number of civilians employed by the consortium AWE Management Ltd is 155.</p>","Sevenoaks","Michael Fallon","26655","2016-02-15T15:51:00.95Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451617/answer","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451617/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451617/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-02-09","Defence: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what average wage was earned by civilians employed by (a) the Ministry of Defence and its trading bodies and (b) contractors at (i) AWE Aldermaston, (ii) AWE Burghfield, (iii) BAE Systems Maritime-Submarines at Barrow-in-Furness, (iv) Babcock at Devonport and (v) Rolls-Royce at Raynesway, Derby in the last 12 months.","false","Biography information for Neil Gray","Airdrie and Shotts","Neil Gray","26656"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451618","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-02-18","<p>The Foreign and Commonwealth Office does not hold information on this issue. However, according to the Israeli Non-Government Office (NGO) Military Court Watch, 422 Palestinian children were held in Israeli military detention as of 31 December, 2015. According to figures provided by the Israeli Prison Service, 148 children are being held inside detention facilities inside of Israel and 274 children are being held in the Occupied Palestinian Territories. According to the Palestinian human rights NGO, Addameer, there are no children being detained as Palestinian prisoners.</p><p>We are concerned about the treatment of Palestinian children in Israeli prisons. We funded an independent report on Children in Military Custody.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2016-02-18T16:35:28.043Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451618/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451618/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451618/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-02-09","Palestinians: Detainees","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what information his Department holds on the number of Palestinian children imprisoned in (a) Palestine and (b) Israel in 2015.","false","Biography information for Shabana Mahmood","Birmingham, Ladywood","Shabana Mahmood","26446"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451619","Ministry of Justice","false","2016-02-15","<p>The Ministry of Justice does not have operational responsibility for coroner services, as they are funded and run by local authorities. The level of funding for the Birmingham and Solihull, Black Country and Coventry coroner services is a matter for the relevant local authorities and the Ministry of Justice holds no information on this.</p><p> </p><p>Statistics for deaths reported to coroners, including deaths in state detention and those subject to Deprivation of Liberty Safeguards, are published annually at <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/coroners-and-burials-statistics" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/coroners-and-burials-statistics</a>.</p><p> </p><p>We do not have information on the number of deaths in state detention reported to coroners in 2010 as this information has only been gathered centrally since 2012. The statistics for 2015 will be published in due course.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage","26444 ; 26445","2016-02-15T12:04:27.18Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451619/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451619/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451619/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2016-02-09","Coroners: West Midlands","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what the level of funding was for coroners in the coroner areas of (a) Birmingham and Solihull, (b) the Black Country and (c) Coventry in (i) 2009-10 and (ii) 2015-16; and what assessment he has made of the implications for such funding of trends in the number of cases dealt with by coroners between those two years.","false","Biography information for Shabana Mahmood","Birmingham, Ladywood","Shabana Mahmood","26447"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451620","Department of Health","false","2016-02-15","<p>The Department does not hold this information.</p>","Ipswich","Ben Gummer",,"2016-02-15T09:54:56.323Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451620/answer","Biography information for Ben Gummer","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451620/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451620/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-02-09","Pathology: Qualifications","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many pathologists qualified to conduct postmortems there were in (a) 2010 and (b) 2015.","false","Biography information for Shabana Mahmood","Birmingham, Ladywood","Shabana Mahmood","26443"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451621","Ministry of Justice","false","2016-02-15","<p>The Ministry of Justice does not have operational responsibility for coroner services, as they are funded and run by local authorities. The level of funding for the Birmingham and Solihull, Black Country and Coventry coroner services is a matter for the relevant local authorities and the Ministry of Justice holds no information on this.</p><p> </p><p>Statistics for deaths reported to coroners, including deaths in state detention and those subject to Deprivation of Liberty Safeguards, are published annually at <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/coroners-and-burials-statistics" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/coroners-and-burials-statistics</a>.</p><p> </p><p>We do not have information on the number of deaths in state detention reported to coroners in 2010 as this information has only been gathered centrally since 2012. The statistics for 2015 will be published in due course.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage","26445 ; 26447","2016-02-15T12:04:27.067Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451621/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451621/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451621/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2016-02-09","Prisoners: Death","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many referrals were made to coroners in England which relate to people who have died in state detention in (a) 2010 and (b) 2015.","false","Biography information for Shabana Mahmood","Birmingham, Ladywood","Shabana Mahmood","26444"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451622","Ministry of Justice","false","2016-02-15","<p>The Ministry of Justice does not have operational responsibility for coroner services, as they are funded and run by local authorities. The level of funding for the Birmingham and Solihull, Black Country and Coventry coroner services is a matter for the relevant local authorities and the Ministry of Justice holds no information on this.</p><p> </p><p>Statistics for deaths reported to coroners, including deaths in state detention and those subject to Deprivation of Liberty Safeguards, are published annually at <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/coroners-and-burials-statistics" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/coroners-and-burials-statistics</a>.</p><p> </p><p>We do not have information on the number of deaths in state detention reported to coroners in 2010 as this information has only been gathered centrally since 2012. The statistics for 2015 will be published in due course.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage","26444 ; 26447","2016-02-15T12:04:27.12Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451622/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451622/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451622/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2016-02-09","Mental Capacity","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many referrals were made to coroners in England in respect of people who  died in a care home or hospital and were subject to Deprivation of Liberty Safeguards in 2015.","false","Biography information for Shabana Mahmood","Birmingham, Ladywood","Shabana Mahmood","26445"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451623","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2016-02-22","<p>We intend to consult this year on the future design of the Energy Company Obligation, including the use of Government data to help identify fuel poor households in greatest need of support. The Government is considering how access to data, including that held by the Valuation Office Agency, could be improved for the purposes of providing assistance to fuel poor households.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom",,"2016-02-22T12:57:57.85Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451623/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451623/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451623/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2016-02-09","Fuel Poverty","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, what progress is being made on introducing data sharing arrangements between the Valuation Office Agency and the Department for Work and Pensions that would allow the up-front identification of fuel poor households; and whether she plans that those arrangements will be introduced in 2017 in time to support the new energy efficiency obligation announced in the Spending Review and Autumn Statement 2015.","false","Biography information for Angus Brendan MacNeil","Na h-Eileanan an Iar","Angus Brendan MacNeil","26510"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451624","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-02-22","<p>The information requested is not readily available and to provide it would incur disproportionate cost.</p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2016-02-22T12:32:29.647Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451624/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451624/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451624/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-02-09","Children: Maintenance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many outstanding cases the Child Support Agency have relating to the tracing of a non-resident parent.","false","Biography information for Mr Nigel Evans","Ribble Valley","Mr Nigel Evans","26503"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451625","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-02-22","<p>There are no plans to work with the police in order to try and pursue the debt of non-resident parents.</p><p><strong> </strong></p><p>We have at our disposal a range of strong enforcement powers, intended to ensure all parents fulfil their financial responsibilities towards their children. We are using all of the powers available to us where it is appropriate to do so. These powers include deducting maintenance directly from earnings, sharing information about non-compliance with credit reference agencies, instructing bailiffs to collect arrears or seize goods, forcing the sale of property, commitment to prison and disqualification from driving.</p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2016-02-22T12:17:29.333Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451625/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451625/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451625/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-02-09","Children: Maintenance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what plans the Child Support Agency has to work more closely with the police in order to pursue the debt of non-resident parents.","false","Biography information for Mr Nigel Evans","Ribble Valley","Mr Nigel Evans","26502"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451626","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-02-22","<p>The Government set up a new Child Maintenance scheme in 2012 to address historic failings in the 1993 and 2003 schemes. The Child Support Agency stopped accepting new applications in 2013. The operational priority of the statutory service is to collect money for children who will benefit from regular ongoing maintenance payments today, rather than prioritising the pursuit of historic arrears in cases where the children have now grown up.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The number of CSA cases paying towards an arrears liability is given in the table below.</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Quarter ending:</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Number of Cases with an Arrears Liability</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Paying Towards Arrears</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>% Paying Towards Arrears</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Mar-12</strong></p></td><td><p>1,188,200</p></td><td><p>275,700</p></td><td><p>23.2%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Mar-13</strong></p></td><td><p>1,240,200</p></td><td><p>289,700</p></td><td><p>23.4%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Mar-14</strong></p></td><td><p>1,274,200</p></td><td><p>283,100</p></td><td><p>22.2%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Mar-15</strong></p></td><td><p>1,232,000</p></td><td><p>242,900</p></td><td><p>19.7%</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p><strong> </strong></p><p>This and further information is available in Table 10 of the latest Quarterly Summary of Statistics which can be accessed online at:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/479356/csa-quarterly-summary-stats-sept-2015.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/479356/csa-quarterly-summary-stats-sept-2015.pdf</a></p><p> </p><p><strong> </strong></p><p>Notes:</p><p>1) Data not available prior to March 2012</p><p>2) Figures are rounded to the nearest 100.</p><p><strong>3) </strong>A case is counted as paying towards arrears if they had an outstanding arrears balance at the end of the previous quarter and no liability to pay regular maintenance over the current quarter but money is being received via the collection service, or if the full regular liability has been satisfied in the quarter and additional payments have been received.</p><p><strong> </strong></p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2016-02-22T12:27:06.017Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451626/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451626/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451626/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-02-09","Children: Maintenance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, in how many cases the Child Support Agency has been successful in pursuing the debt of a non-resident parent in the last five years.","false","Biography information for Mr Nigel Evans","Ribble Valley","Mr Nigel Evans","26608"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451627","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-02-16","<p>At the programme level it is approximately 10% of the budget with a further contingency fund being available centrally. Risk management is an on-going process which is forward-looking by its very nature. Financial risk provision is a dynamic element of the overall programme budget; as risks are identified, managed, mitigated and retired the associated risk provision at various levels in the Department changes.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"2016-02-16T16:01:06.007Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451627/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451627/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451627/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-02-09","Nuclear Submarines: Expenditure","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, with reference to the oral statement of 6 March 2014, Official Report, column 1077, on nuclear submarines, how much his Department set aside for financial risk provision within the submarine programme budget in each of the last six years.","false","Biography information for Emily Thornberry","Islington South and Finsbury","Emily Thornberry","26527"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451628","Attorney General","false","2016-02-22","<p>At the February European Council the Government negotiated a new settlement, giving the United Kingdom a special status in a reformed European Union. The Government's view is that the UK will be stronger, safer and better off remaining in a reformed EU.</p>","Kenilworth and Southam","Jeremy Wright","26440","2016-02-22T16:38:28.737Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451628/answer","Biography information for Jeremy Wright","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451628/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451628/answer",,,,,"88","Attorney General","Attorney General","2016-02-09","Human Rights","1","House of Commons","To ask the Attorney General, if he will make an assessment of the potential effect on the promotion of human rights of the UK leaving the EU.","false","Biography information for Karl Turner","Kingston upon Hull East","Karl Turner","26439"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451629","Attorney General","false","2016-02-22","<p>At the February European Council the Government negotiated a new settlement, giving the United Kingdom a special status in a reformed European Union. The Government's view is that the UK will be stronger, safer and better off remaining in a reformed EU.</p>","Kenilworth and Southam","Jeremy Wright","26439","2016-02-22T16:38:28.8Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451629/answer","Biography information for Jeremy Wright","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451629/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451629/answer",,,,,"88","Attorney General","Attorney General","2016-02-09","European Arrest Warrants","1","House of Commons","To ask the Attorney General, whether he has made an assessment of the potential effect of the UK leaving the EU on the application and implementation of the European Arrest Warrant.","false","Biography information for Karl Turner","Kingston upon Hull East","Karl Turner","26440"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451630","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2016-02-22","<p>The inter-ministerial group on Clean Growth meets as and when required and its members include ministers and officials from the relevant departments, including the Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, the Department of Energy and Climate Change, the Department for Communities and Local Government, the Department for Transport and the Department for Business, Innovation and Skills.</p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart",,"2016-02-22T13:24:02.303Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451630/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451630/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451630/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2016-02-09","Clean Growth Ministerial Group","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, on how many occasions the Clean Growth Committee has met to discuss air quality to date; and who attended each such meeting.","false","Biography information for Kerry McCarthy","Bristol East","Kerry McCarthy","26611"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451631","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-02-19","<p>We have not been able to obtain access to Mr Foroughi since his detention in May 2011. The Iranian Government does not recognise dual nationality for Iranian citizens. Our requests for consular access to detainees have been rejected on these grounds. We regularly express our concerns about all of our consular cases at high level with the Iranian Government.</p><p>Prime Minister David Cameron raised these issues in a letter to President Rouhani on 19 October and again in a telephone call on 19 January. Most recently this was raised by the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, my right hon. Friend the Member for Runnymede and Weybridge (Mr Hammond) during Foreign Minister Zarif’s visit to London on 5 February. I am also keeping a close interest in Mr Foroughi’s case, having recently met with his son in London on 1 December and 14 January.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2016-02-19T10:35:29.503Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451631/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451631/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451631/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-02-09","Kamal Foroughi","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what assessment his Department has made of the conditions in which Kamal Foroughi is being held in Evin Prison, Iran.","false","Biography information for Tom Brake","Carshalton and Wallington","Tom Brake","26413"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451632","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-02-18","<p>We remain concerned about continued reports of slavery in Mauritania, and about the modest sentences handed down in the few successful prosecutions for slavery offences. We welcome the establishment of three courts with specific responsibility for slavery cases. We continue to monitor this topic closely. We regularly raise our concerns with the Mauritanian authorities in the UK and in Nouakchott, and meet human rights and anti-slavery campaigners to discuss the subject.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2016-02-18T10:03:30.517Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451632/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451632/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451632/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-02-09","Mauritania: Slavery","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, whether his Department has made an assessment of the prevalence of slavery in Mauritania.","false","Biography information for Tom Brake","Carshalton and Wallington","Tom Brake","26412"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451633","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-02-22","<p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p><p>The Government plans to publish the Impact Assessment, including results of the family test, shortly.</p><p><strong> </strong></p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2016-02-22T17:45:22.733Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451633/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451633/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451633/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-02-09","Sunday Trading: Families","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, how his Department has applied the family test to its proposals for draft legislation to devolve Sunday trading regulations; and what the outcome of the application of that test was.","false","Biography information for Fiona Bruce","Congleton","Fiona Bruce","26577"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451634","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-02-22","<p>My Department has carried out an assessment of the impacts of devolving the power to extend Sunday trading hours and this will be published.</p><p><strong> </strong></p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2016-02-22T17:24:53.413Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451634/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451634/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451634/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-02-09","Sunday Trading","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what assessment his Department has made of the effects of its proposals to devolve Sunday trading regulations on the displacement of trade from small to large stores.","false","Biography information for Fiona Bruce","Congleton","Fiona Bruce","26578"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451635","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-02-29","<p>The Department does not hold full data from this consultation broken down by specific question as a large portion of respondents chose to respond in their own words rather than addressing the consultation questions directly, and/or did not indicate the type of organisation they represented.</p><p><strong> </strong></p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2016-02-29T10:21:22.42Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451635/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451635/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451635/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-02-09","Sunday Trading: Public Consultation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what (a) number and (b) proportion of those respondents to his Department's consultation, Devolving Sunday trading rules, published on 5 August 2015, answered (i) yes, (ii) no and (iii) otherwise to Question 1 in that consultation.","false","Biography information for Fiona Bruce","Congleton","Fiona Bruce","26600"
