"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451642","HM Treasury","false","2016-02-22","<p>At the Summer Budget 2015 the Chancellor announced that the dividend tax credit will be replaced by a new £5,000 tax-free dividend allowance from April 2016. A Tax Information and Impact Note setting out expected impacts was published on 9 December on GOV.UK. Impact assessments have been produced for all measures in the Finance Bill 2016.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2016-02-22T17:32:54.007Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451642/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451642/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451642/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-02-09","Investment Income: Taxation","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, whether he has conducted an impact assessment of (a) the proposed changes to the dividend tax system and (b) other measures in the Finance Bill 2016 on lower-earning micro-business owners.","false","Biography information for David Warburton","Somerton and Frome","David Warburton","26605"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451643","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-02-22","<p>The Government has a long-standing policy not to comment on intelligence matters.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"2016-02-22T16:10:55.52Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451643/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451643/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451643/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-02-09","Libya: Deployment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, whether personnel from Reaper Squadrons 39 and 13 attended military meetings in Tobruk between 18 January and 31 January 2016.","false","Biography information for Mr David Davis","Haltemprice and Howden","Mr David Davis","26593"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451644","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-02-22","<p>The UK is considering, with partner nations, how we can best support the new Libyan government, including in terms of capacity building and security sector reform. No decisions have been made about the future deployment of any British military forces to Libya as part of an international coalition force.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"2016-02-22T16:12:14.227Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451644/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451644/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451644/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-02-09","Libya: Deployment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what assessment he has made of the implications for his policies of the proposal from the Italian government (a) to deploy 1,000 British troops to Libya and (b) for Italian Reaper drones to conduct target acquisition in Libya for the purpose of joint strike operations with the US and UK.","false","Biography information for Mr David Davis","Haltemprice and Howden","Mr David Davis","26592"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451645","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-02-22","<p>No personnel directly from 39 Squadron or 13 Squadron are currently embedded with the US armed forces. However, from the Reaper force as a whole, there are currently six Royal Air Force personnel embedded with the United States Air Force. There are no Reaper force personnel serving with the French or Italian armed forces.</p><p> </p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"2016-02-22T16:13:02.017Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451645/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451645/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451645/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-02-09","Air Force: Deployment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, whether personnel from Reaper Squadrons 39 and 13 are currently embedded with (a) US, (b) French and (c) Italian armed forces.","false","Biography information for Mr David Davis","Haltemprice and Howden","Mr David Davis","26594"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451646","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-02-22","<p>No personnel from 39 Squadron or 13 Squadron have been deployed to Sicily.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"2016-02-22T16:14:14.07Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451646/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451646/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451646/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-02-09","Italy: Deployment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, whether personnel from Reaper Squadrons 39 and 13 have been deployed to Sicily.","false","Biography information for Mr David Davis","Haltemprice and Howden","Mr David Davis","26553"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451647","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-05-11","<p>The benefits of devolution to areas that have agreed devolution deals with the Government will be significant and far-reaching. Local leaders will be given direct control over the levers of growth in their economies, with the most ambitious deals including new powers over adult skills and transport budgets, and substantial, long-term investment funds. For example, the West Midlands will receive over £1 billion of additional investment to deliver locally determined growth priorities. By providing local partners with greater control over key policies and resources, devolution deals offer places more of the tools they need to drive forward growth for the benefit of the whole local economy.</p>","Stockton South","James Wharton",,"2016-05-11T16:41:15.26Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451647/answer","Biography information for James Wharton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451647/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451647/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-02-09","Local Government: Devolution","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what assessment he has made of the benefit to local economies of Devolution Deals.","false","Biography information for Julian Knight","Solihull","Julian Knight","26654"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451648","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-02-17","<p>Mineral planning authorities have a responsibility to consider planning applications for shale gas exploration under the Town and Country Planning regime. Planning law requires that applications for planning permission must be determined in accordance with the development plan for the local authority area, unless material considerations indicate otherwise. The Government has taken steps to ensure this locally led regime is effective, as set out in Written Ministerial Statements of 16 September, HCWS201 and HCWS202. This includes making available £1.2 million to ensure mineral planning authorities have adequate resource to reach timely decisions.</p><p>Community involvement in planning applications and people’s safety and the environment will remain paramount. No decision has been made to take shale gas exploration out of this local authority led process.</p>","Stockton South","James Wharton",,"2016-02-17T14:34:25.513Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451648/answer","Biography information for James Wharton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451648/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451648/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-02-09","Fracking: Planning Permission","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what his policy is on removing from local authorities powers to veto planning applications for fracking.","false","Biography information for Sir David Crausby","Bolton North East","Mr David Crausby","26676"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451649","Department of Health","false","2016-02-17","<p>The NHS Bowel Cancer Screening programme is a biennial programme, in which eligible men and women are invited every two years to be screened.</p><p> </p><p>Roll out of the programme began in 2006 and completed in 2010 offering screening from the ages of 60-69. The Programme then extended the screening age up to 74.</p><p> </p><p>In the last five years, over 19 million men and women have been invited to take part in the NHS Bowel Cancer Screening Programme.</p><p> </p><p>Since the Programmes introduction in 2006, over 24,000 cancers have been detected and over 146,000 patients have been managed for polyps, including polyp removal.</p><p> </p><p>The NHS Bowel Cancer Screening programme will be publishing further data with regards to local areas at a later date.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison",,"2016-02-17T14:41:52.74Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451649/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451649/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451649/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-02-09","Bowel Cancer: Older People","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many people in (a) the UK and (b) Bolton have been included in the Bowel Cancer Screening programme for over-60s in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Sir David Crausby","Bolton North East","Mr David Crausby","26677"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451650","Department of Health","false","2016-02-15","<p>The Department’s Ministerial Correspondence and Public Enquiries unit currently employs a total of 31 permanent staff who work on both public and ministerial correspondence. There are also eight non-permanent workers filling vacancies within the unit who also work on public and ministerial correspondence. In 2015 the unit responded to 42,277 letters from hon. Members, Peers and the public.</p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison",,"2016-02-15T10:00:44.923Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451650/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451650/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451650/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-02-09","Department of Health: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many members of staff are employed in the Ministerial correspondence section of his Department.","false","Biography information for Sir David Crausby","Bolton North East","Mr David Crausby","26678"
