"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451675","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-02-29","<p>The Department does not hold full data from this consultation broken down by specific question as a large portion of respondents chose to respond in their own words rather than addressing the consultation questions directly, and/or did not indicate the type of organisation they represented.</p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2016-02-29T10:24:18.493Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451675/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451675/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451675/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-02-09","Sunday Trading: Public Consultation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, how many small businesses responded to the Government's consultation, Devolving Sunday trading rules, published on 5 August 2015; and what (a) number and (b) proportion of those respondents answered (i) yes, (ii) no and (iii) otherwise to Question one of that consultation.","false","Biography information for Martin Vickers","Cleethorpes","Martin Vickers","26602"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451676","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-02-22","<p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p><p>In formulating its final proposals, the Government has carefully considered all the evidence submitted during the consultation process.</p><p><strong> </strong></p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2016-02-22T17:53:50.133Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451676/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451676/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451676/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-02-09","Sunday Trading","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what the implications for his Department's proposals to devolve Sunday trading regulations are of the findings of the recent USDAW survey of shopworkers on levels of opposition to relaxation of current Sunday trading laws.","false","Biography information for Martin Vickers","Cleethorpes","Martin Vickers","26603"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451677","Department of Health","false","2016-02-22","<p>The Food Standards Agency (FSA) has advised us that the safety of caffeine has been reviewed by the European Food Safety Authority, which specified a level of caffeine for children and adolescents which does not raise safety concerns. For a 10-year-old child this is equivalent to the amount of caffeine in one 250 ml can of high caffeine drink.</p><p> </p><p>The FSA does not collect data on the sale of high caffeine drinks and has no plans to restrict the sale of these drinks to children. However, the FSA advises that children and other people who are sensitive to caffeine should consume caffeine only in moderation. High caffeine drinks must be labelled with an advisory statement that they are not recommended for children.</p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison","26545","2016-02-22T12:38:14.537Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451677/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451677/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451677/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-02-09","Energy Drinks: Children","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what data his Department collects on sales of highly caffeinated drinks to children.","false","Biography information for Alison McGovern","Wirral South","Alison McGovern","26544"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451678","Department of Health","false","2016-02-22","<p>The Food Standards Agency (FSA) has advised us that the safety of caffeine has been reviewed by the European Food Safety Authority, which specified a level of caffeine for children and adolescents which does not raise safety concerns. For a 10-year-old child this is equivalent to the amount of caffeine in one 250 ml can of high caffeine drink.</p><p> </p><p>The FSA does not collect data on the sale of high caffeine drinks and has no plans to restrict the sale of these drinks to children. However, the FSA advises that children and other people who are sensitive to caffeine should consume caffeine only in moderation. High caffeine drinks must be labelled with an advisory statement that they are not recommended for children.</p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison","26544","2016-02-22T12:38:14.597Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451678/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451678/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451678/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-02-09","Energy Drinks: Sales","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, if his Department will take steps to reduce sales of highly caffeinated drinks to children.","false","Biography information for Alison McGovern","Wirral South","Alison McGovern","26545"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451679","Department of Health","false","2016-02-22","<p>The Department is currently discussing with key stakeholders the arrangements for formally bringing the Multiple Sclerosis Risk Sharing Scheme to an end. Patients currently receiving drugs as part of the Scheme will continue to do so for as long as this is clinically appropriate for them.</p>","Mid Norfolk","George Freeman",,"2016-02-22T12:29:22.603Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451679/answer","Biography information for George Freeman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451679/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451679/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-02-09","Multiple Sclerosis: Drugs","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, when he intends to make a decision on the closure of the Risk Sharing Scheme; and what provisions his Department plans to put in place for people who are currently accessing drugs via that Scheme.","false","Biography information for Nick Thomas-Symonds","Torfaen","Nick Thomas-Symonds","26606"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451681","Ministry of Justice","false","2016-02-22","<p>There has been one complaint about the standard of the recent consultation on the provision of court and tribunal estate in England and Wales.</p><p>The complaint, received by email, was from a member of the judiciary and related to St Alban’s County Court. It noted that the consultation document was inaccurate as it stated that no enabling work was required at the receiving court, Watford County Court. On investigation, it was determined that some enabling work would be required. The written response to the complaint corrected this inaccuracy. The published consultation response document was updated to present corrected information.</p><p>During the consultation process we were notified about inaccuracies in the consultation documents. These have all been corrected in the published response documents. All decisions were based on correct information together with the careful consideration of the consultation responses.</p><p>The consultation response is available online at <a href="http://www.gov.uk/moj" target="_blank">www.gov.uk/moj</a>.</p>","North West Cambridgeshire","Mr Shailesh Vara",,"2016-02-22T18:00:42.517Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451681/answer","Biography information for Mr Shailesh Vara","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451681/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451681/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2016-02-09","Courts: Closures","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many complaints his Department received about the standard of its recent consultation document on court closures.","false","Biography information for Andy Slaughter","Hammersmith","Andy Slaughter","26452"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451682","Ministry of Justice","false","2016-02-22","<p>The vast majority of incidents are minor in nature and resolved quickly and professionally without injury, damage or disruption to the running of the prison. Each incident is investigated fully to ensure lessons are learnt and best practice in managing incidents is shared across NOMS.</p><p> </p><p>Many incidents at height are relatively short in duration, lasting less than 15 minutes, and take place on netting or over railings. Hostage incidents are relatively rare and in many cases of hostage taking collusion between the perpetrator and victim is suspected. We do not tolerate violence or disorder in our prisons. Prisoners who take part in violent incidents can be referred to the police for prosecution or receive additional time on their sentences following internal adjudication.</p><p> </p><p>The tables attached provide numbers of incidents at height and hostage incidents in each month between March 2014 and December 2015 and broken down by establishment.</p><p> </p><p>Note: These figures have been drawn from the NOMS Incident Reporting System. Care is taken when processing and analysing the returns but the detail collected is subject to the inaccuracies inherent in any large scale recording system. Although the figures are shown to the last case the figures may not be accurate to that level.</p>","South West Bedfordshire","Andrew Selous","26454","2016-02-22T11:19:15.297Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451682/answer","Biography information for Andrew Selous","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451682/answer","26453 - 26454 - Table.xls","26453 - 26454 - Table.xls","incidents at height and hostage incidents - prison","incidents at height and hostage incidents - prison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451682/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2016-02-09","Prisons: Discipline","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many incidents at height have taken place in each prison in each month since March 2014.","false","Biography information for Andy Slaughter","Hammersmith","Andy Slaughter","26453"
