"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451691","Attorney General","false","2016-02-22","<p>At the February European Council the Government negotiated a new settlement, giving the United Kingdom a special status in a reformed European Union. The Government's view is that the UK will be stronger, safer and better off remaining in a reformed EU.</p>","Kenilworth and Southam","Jeremy Wright",,"2016-02-22T16:39:34.377Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451691/answer","Biography information for Jeremy Wright","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451691/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451691/answer",,,,,"88","Attorney General","Attorney General","2016-02-09","UK Membership of EU","1","House of Commons","To ask the Attorney General, what planning his Department has undertaken in the event of the UK voting to leave the EU.","false","Biography information for Mr Douglas Carswell","Clacton","Mr Douglas Carswell","26617"
